				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://automation.isa.org/2017/01/purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications/">AutoQuiz: What is the Purpose of a Breadboard in Electronics Applications?</a> first appeared on the <a rel="nofollow" href="http://automation.isa.org">ISA Interchange</a> blog site.</p>
<div class="pf-content"><div class="woo-sc-box  normal   "><em>AutoQuiz is edited by <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/in/joeldon/" target="_blank">Joel Don</a>, ISA&#8217;s community manager.</em></div>
<p>Today&#8217;s automation industry quiz question comes from the ISA <a href="http://bit.ly/1Sa42PT" target="_blank">Certified Control Systems Technician (CCST) program</a>. Certified Control System Technicians calibrate, document, troubleshoot, and repair/replace instrumentation for systems that measure and control level, temperature, pressure, flow, and other process variables. <a href="http://bit.ly/1Sa42PT" target="_blank">Click this link</a> for information about the CCST program. This question comes from the Level I study guide, Domain 3, Troubleshooting. Level I represents a professional who has a five-year total of education, training, and/or experience.</p>
<p><img data-attachment-id="21058" data-permalink="http://automation.isa.org/2017/01/purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications/autoquiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications/" data-orig-file="https://i1.wp.com/automation.isa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/AutoQuiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications.jpg?fit=480%2C270" data-orig-size="480,270" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="autoquiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i1.wp.com/automation.isa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/AutoQuiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications.jpg?fit=300%2C169" data-large-file="https://i1.wp.com/automation.isa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/AutoQuiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications.jpg?fit=480%2C270" class="aligncenter  wp-image-21058" src="https://i1.wp.com/automation.isa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/AutoQuiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications.jpg?resize=772%2C434" alt="autoquiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/automation.isa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/AutoQuiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications.jpg?w=480 480w, https://i1.wp.com/automation.isa.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/AutoQuiz-20170113-purpose-breadboard-electronics-applications.jpg?resize=300%2C169 300w" sizes="(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></p>
<p><strong>A breadboard is</strong>:</p>
<p>a) a data routing circuit<br />
b) used to design or test electronic circuits<br />
c) a code-converting circuit<br />
d) a temporary binary storage area<br />
e) none of the above</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Â Â Â  <div class='dropshadowboxes-container dropshadowboxes-center ' style='width:100%;'>
                            <div class='dropshadowboxes-drop-shadow dropshadowboxes-rounded-corners dropshadowboxes-inside-and-outside-shadow dropshadowboxes-lifted-both dropshadowboxes-effect-default' style='width:500px; border: 1px solid #dddddd; height:; background-color:#fffbaa;    '>
                            <span class="collapseomatic " id="id2775"  tabindex="0" title="<strong>Click Here to Reveal the Answer</strong>"    ><strong>Click Here to Reveal the Answer</strong></span><div id="target-id2775" class="collapseomatic_content ">
<p>A breadboard is a construction base for prototyping of electronics. Originally it was literally a breadboard, a polished piece of wood used for slicing bread.</p>
<p>The correct answer is <strong>B</strong>.</p>
